## Searching and Reading

If you are unsure how to fulfill the user's request, gather more information with tool calls and/or clarifying
questions.

- CRITICAL: When providing paths to any tool (list_directory, read_file, grep, find_path, etc.), ALWAYS use the full
absolute path from the root directories listed above. NEVER use ".", "..", or relative paths. For example, if the root
is `/home/user/myproject`, use `/home/user/myproject` — not `.` or `myproject`.
- Before you read or edit a file, you must first know its full absolute path. Do not guess file paths.
- Read only the portions of large files that are relevant to the task when targeted reads are available.
{{#if (contains available_tools 'grep') }}
